  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ 425°F/ Gas 7</p><p>Shred the <strong>red cabbage </strong>(not too finely), discard the root</p><p>Remove some <strong>butter</strong> from the fridge and set it aside to soften</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1582891217192-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1582891217192-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1582891217192-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1582891217192-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1582891217192-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>shredded red cabbage </strong>to a baking tray with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and give everything a good mix up</p><p>Layer the <strong>Cumberland sausages</strong> over the top of the cabbage and put the tray in the oven for an initial 10 min</p><p>Tip: Cooking for 4? Use 2 trays!</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1582891221795-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1582891221795-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1582891221795-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1582891221795-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1582891221795-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Whilst everything is in the oven, wash the <strong>leek<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span> </strong>carefully to remove any grit from between the leaves, then top, tail and slice in half lengthways and chop into 8 <span class=\"text-danger\">[16]</span> pieces</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1582891226294-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1582891226294-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1582891226294-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1582891226294-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1582891226294-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Strip the <strong>thyme</strong> and <strong>rosemary leaves</strong> from their stems and discard the stems</p><p>Boil a kettle</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1582891231675-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1582891231675-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1582891231675-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1582891231675-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1582891231675-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the sausages and red cabbage have had an initial 10 min, remove the tray from the oven</p><p>Add the <strong>chopped leek </strong>with<strong> </strong>a<strong> </strong>drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> and a crack of <strong>black pepper</strong>, then<strong> </strong>sprinkle over the <strong>rosemary leaves</strong> and <strong>half </strong>the <strong>thyme leaves </strong>(save the rest for later!)</p><p>Return the tray to the oven for a further 6-8 min or until everything is beginning to brown</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1582891236520-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1582891236520-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1582891236520-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1582891236520-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1582891236520-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, rip the <strong>ciabatta roll<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> roughly into croutons</p><p>Add the <strong>croutons</strong> to a bowl with a knob of <strong>butter</strong> and the <strong>remaining thyme leaves</strong></p><p>Mix everything together so that the croutons are evenly coated – these are your <strong>thyme croutons</strong></p><p>Dissolve the<strong> beef stock mix</strong> in<strong> </strong>250ml<span class=\"text-danger\"> [450ml] </span><strong>boiled water </strong>with the <strong>green tomato chutney </strong>– this is your <strong>stock</strong></p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1582891240341-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1582891240341-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1582891240341-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1582891240341-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1582891240341-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>thyme croutons</strong> to the tray</p><p>Return the tray to the oven for a final 8-10 min or until the sausages are cooked through (no pink meat!) and everything is golden - this is your <strong>sausage, red cabbage & leek tray bake</strong></p><p>Meanwhile, heat a large, wide-based pan with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil </strong>over a medium heat and once hot, add 1/2 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[1 tbsp]</span><strong> flour</strong> and cook for 1 min</p><p>Add the<strong> stock </strong>and whisk until combined and cook for 3-4 min or until thickened to a gravy-like consistency</p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1582891244693-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1582891244693-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1582891244693-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1582891244693-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1582891244693-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>sausage</strong>,<strong> red cabbage & leek tray bake </strong>in bowls and drizzle over the <strong>green tomato gravy</strong></p><p>Season with a crack of <strong>black pepper</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8,
